On 9/16/11, Sandy Panico &lt;magicquartz@...&gt; wrote:
&gt; Straight Shot turns to Wing Caliber as does Rattrap.  Yet she is the first
&gt; to speak up.
&gt;
&gt; &quot; That&#39;s a good question, I&#39;m happy you&#39;re willing ta hear us out.  Leo is
&gt; missing something most important and it&#39;s something Tucson has more than
&gt; enough ta go around.  A heart.  I just don&#39;t see that in Leo and neither
&gt; does Rattrap.
&gt;
&gt; Rattrap nods.
&gt;
&gt; &quot; Yeah, the first time I met Tucson I knew he was special.  I just don&#39;t
&gt; have that feeling around Leo.  As bad tempered as he is, he&#39;s got more
&gt; compassion ta go around.  And he believes in us on a personal level.  Leo is
&gt; okay but he ain&#39;t got what really matters.&quot;
&gt;
&gt; They both put a paw over their chest.  Straight Shot speaks up again.
&gt;
&gt; &quot; When it all comes down to it, what matters most is what&#39;s in our hearts
&gt; and a leader without a heart is like not having one at all.  And that&#39;s why
&gt; we have a hard time with Leo.  If Tucson was here, he may have asked the
&gt; same question.  Tucson has a really big heart and to me, he IS A LEADER.&quot;

&lt;NEW&gt;

There was a small smile on WINGCALIBER&#39;s face as he listened. &quot;I can
remember when LEO PRIME was young, back when he found by his father,
who was back then LIO PRIME.&quot; There was a slight shrug, &quot;Back then the
Leo we know was just known as Leo jr.&quot;

SANTON nodded as he sat down his pack and came over as well. &quot;Yes, Leo
jr was much like Tuscon, young, exuberant, full of energy and even
compassion.&quot; SANTON looked whistful as he thought of the past.

&quot;He was much like that.&quot; WINGCALIBER said as he spoke again. &quot;But that
was many years and many battles ago. Since then he has become a prime,
and the old Lio Prime became Lio Convoy and eventually Leo himself
became a Prime.&quot;

There was a compassionate look from SANTON, &quot;He is going through the
natural growing pains of a leader.&quot; He nodded, &quot;Tuscon is a new Prime
and has been a warrior for most of that time, he has not felt the
stings of betrayal yet from the Predacons that Leo has.&quot;

WINGCALIBER nodded, &quot;Do not judge him so harshly because he doesn&#39;t
trust the Predacons. I have watched him grow as a warrior and a
leader, and I have seen the forces that have shaped him.&quot;

SANTON grunted, &quot;Most leaders, most Primes start off much the way
Tuscon is now, full of life and full of trust. &quot; He nodded, &quot;I have
served under a few myself. but if not careful the weight of having men
die under your command, the weight of having to make the choices that
would send men to their deaths can be a burden that changes you.&quot;

Gesturing at the door that RAT TRAP and STRAIGHT SHOT had just come
through, &quot;He is a different leader than Tuscon because he has been
through different things, but that doesn&#39;t make him a bad leader, only
different. Perhaps Tuscon would have made ultimately different
choices, but that is the job of a leader, to make those hard choices
despite what everyone else wants . . . despite what he may himself
want to do.&quot;

The words of SANTON and WINGCALIBER are not harsh or accusatory, but
reasoning and questioning, asking STRAIGHT SHOT and RAT TRAP to do the
very things they are asking of LEO PRIME, to trust, even when it
doesn&#39;t always make sense to.

